<Author>vinnychase
<Content>Good Hotel Stayed at the Caribe Hilton in late July 2008. In my stay I was able to experience two towers of the hotel. First they put me in the Main Tower. This part of the hotel was just ok. It was older, but the rooms looked renovated with new furniture  large bathrooms with two sinks  an overhead rain shower. The bad part of the room was my view looked at a construction site,  the noise woke me up every morning. After 2 nights of my air conditioning breaking down  the staff trying to fix it, I asked for a room change. The Hilton staff was somewhat unwilling to do this (said the hotel was booked  could not change rooms), but after talking to a manager I was able to be moved into the Executive Tower. This part of the hotel is much nicer. The rooms are newer, although bathrooms are smaller (no rain shower) than the older tower. I had an awesome view of the beach  ocean. This tower also has the executive lounge where they have breakfast every morning (bagels, fruit, pastries, cereal, coffee)  hors devours after 5pm. In both towers the rooms I had featured safes  small fridges. The resort part of the hotel is nice. They have a 2 tiered pool, hammocks, a gym  tennis courts. The private beach is a little small,  the water was somewhat choppy. Old San Juan is around 15 min by bus  the bus stop is a 2 min walk from the hotel. Condado is about a 15-20 min walk from the hotel. If you take a cab its about $15 to each destination.One of the problems with the hotel is the area. Besides the resort  neighboring Normandie hotel, there is not much around. If you want to eat quick, the only options to eat close to the hotel besides the overpriced hotel restaurants is Subway Sandwich across the street.After visiting Condado, I wished I stayed there because of proximity to restaurants  nightlife. There are many nice Casino/Resort Hotels there, and a ton of restaurants on that strip within walking distance. So, if you're a person who doesn鈥檛 want to walk, take a cab, or bus every time you want to eat stay in Condado.Overall, my stay at the Caribe Hilton was decent. Although, I'm not sure if it would have been as good had I not been able to switch rooms  have access to the breakfast lounge. Like I said, if I was to stay in around the San Juan area again, I would probably stay in Condado. Extra Info: You will be charged a resort fee every day of your stay. Also, had some good pizza at Via Appia in Condado  if you're looking for close nightlife to the hotel the La Concha in Condado is nice. The lobby  pool of this hotel have a Miami nightlife feel. Good looking crowd, good music. Must do tours:The Rainforest TourThe Biobay Tour (watch your hand glow in the water!) 
