<Author>Mike_Weatherford
<Content>Okay room, great beach We chose the Caribe Hilton as the hotel to spend the night at prior to the cruise. I tried on several occasions to get one of the great rates that others had reported by using Priceline.com, but was never able to get my bid accepted. Finally, about a month or so out, I booked an ocean view room at full price. We arrived at 3:00 pm, only to find out our room wasn鈥檛 ready yet 鈥?which was to be somewhat expected, as our reservations stated the room would be ready by 4:00. We were told we could use the changing facilities and the pool area while we were waiting if we wanted. Our room was made available to us promptly at 4:00 pm. We were in the 鈥渙lder鈥?section of the hotel, and the hallway smelled slightly musty. The room felt somewhat dated, and probably not what I would normally expect for a high end hotel (and a high price tag). It was however in good repair, and more than adequate for our one night stay. I have read that if you complain, you may get upgraded to one of the newer rooms, but again, we were only here for one night, and the room was more than adequate. The grounds however were stunning! The beach and pool areas were immaculate. We spent the early evening, and the next morning snorkeling in the beach swimming area, and were surprised by the number of fish we saw. One word of caution: If you plan to eat at the hotel, plan on dropping some serious coin, even for a hamburger ($16.50 as I recall). Never fear though, there is a Subway just around the corner, and a Starbucks in the hotel for some reasonable breakfast snacks. Check out time was noon, so around eleven we checked out, and stored our bags in the lobby area so that we could do a little sight seeing down town before boarding the cruise ship. If you are looking for some beach time, this may be a good choice for you. If you are just looking for a place to lay your head, find something cheaper - unless of coarse you are willing to pony up for one of the executive rooms! 
