<Author>SuzyNy
<Content>Disappointed Hello-We just got back from a week at the Caribe Hilton. My husband  I were there from April 25 to May 2nd. This is a big hotel with over 800 rooms. Check in time is 4pm  check out is noon. There is the main building (original building)  the tower section. Try to stay in the tower section, as these rooms were supposedly newly renovated. We stayed on the 9th floor of the main building. We were supposed to have an ocean view. The rooms are not directly facing the water, so we had a side view. Unfortunately also overlooking the top of the building  had to deal with noise from some sort of motor. We were offered to make a move, but had to wait a few days-so we stayed where we were-but did not relax sitting on the patio (which was small anyway). The room could have used some 鈥淯pdating鈥? It does have a coffeemaker, un-stocked refrigerator, a safe, ironing board, iron  blow dryer. You can order room service, keep in mind they charge you an extra 15% gratuity, plus $3.00 delivery charge~ a 陆 grapefruit cost $5.50, a pint of Haagen Daaz was $14. There is also pay per view to order on the tv in the room, but they charge about $13-$15 to watch a movie. So stick with the tv choices. The plus, if you had a laptop they did have in room a high speed internet connection. The beach is very small  does look like it was a man-made beach. Yes it is private  they made a wall of rocks to keep the water calm. Not a lot of space on the beach, so there is a cement decking where a lot of people chose to relax. You can rent an umbrella, floats, snorkeling mask($10 hour) etc. There is also a shaded area with a few hammocks. There is a multi level pool  two Jacuzzis on one side of the hotel, the other side had a smaller pool  jacuzzi. There is a dock you can walk out  look at the fish-you can feed them left over bread (ask at the towel hut). There is a pretty tropical garden with swans  other birds  koi swimming on the side of the hotel. After being used to going to 鈥淎ll-Inclusive鈥?resorts, this was a BIG shock to us on the prices of food  drinks. They did have a few restaurants to choose from-鈥淢orton鈥檚 Steakhouse鈥? 鈥淢adrid-San Juan鈥?Spanish), 鈥淩otisserie Il Giardino鈥?Northern Italian),鈥滾emongrass鈥?Pan Asian Latino), 鈥淧almeras鈥?offers buffet dining options also, breakfast was $20.50 per person, 鈥淥las Health Bar鈥? 鈥淎tlantico鈥?snack bar dining outside)  a 鈥淪tarbucks鈥? They also had the 鈥淥asis Bar鈥?inside with nightly entertainment  a small swim up bar in the pool 鈥?not that big of an area-more of a walk up bar in the water with stools. The food we ate there was good鈥?but very expensive!!! You can walk to a 鈥淪ubway鈥?about 5 minute walk- but they are doing some work on that street  there is a horrible odor-so that was not an option for us. You should try to get the 鈥淓xecutive鈥?plan-as they offer you a continental breakfast in the morning, cookies  fruit in the afternoon, hor doeuvres in the evening  desserts later. You also get free coffee, tea, soda, juice  water there. Also there is a computer to check your emails. There is a nice BIG health club with 30 cardiovascular  circuit training machines-treadmills,steppers,ellipticals,bicycles,rowing machine,versa climber,free weights  鈥淔lex Fitness Circuit Training System鈥? They do offer babysitting  there is a kids club, game room, playground(which we did not have use for). They had a daily schedule of activities, but unfortunately it rained for most of our trip, so we did not partake. There is a spa as well, offering massages,facials,body  water therapies. They have a car rental place  some stores(drugstore type store, gift shop, upscale boutiques). They have a travel desk-which again seemed pricey. We did the Camuey Caves  observatory-about $83 a person. The caves were okay, the observatory was a waste-they don鈥檛 explain about anything. My husband wanted to go fishing 鈥?he had a lot of problems arranging that. That is not a popular place to go out fishing. He do go out for a half a day  they did not catch anything, plus it was about $200 for himself to share a boat. It gets expensive traveling 鈥?the taxis charge a few dollars extra from the hotel to go someplace. Most taxi rides are about $15 plus tip. Try to take the bus to Old San Juan, for 50 cents. Really is not much in walking distance  because of all the construction, we chose not to walk. This was not an issue though, as we were concerned. Maybe because of all the rain we had, they were not working. If money is not an issue  a small beach is alright 鈥?then I guess if you stay in the tower section this would be alright-seems more of a place to go for business meetings not a real relaxing, beautiful vacation. Everything there is very expensive  overall did not find most of the people friendly. As for us, we would not go back again. 
