<Content>Enjoyed our trip The joy to see all my parents and players happy and to thank me for this wonderful hotel was remarkable. Our team is from Los Angeles, CA. and we were in a baseball tournament in Puerto Rico. Our stay at the hotel was wonderful having 10 families I needed to have a nice place for them for 10 days. I highly recommend the Caribe. The rooms we had were beautiful we stayed at the Newer tower some people have posted pictures here and that helped me to know before we checked in. In some cases it may be an extra fee but well worth it, I offered the plan to the parents and some took it and others didnt but they were all pleased. The showers are beautiful and roomy. The rooms are clean and well worth it to get the ocean view. If you plan to vacation you should always either work overtime or save those bonuses so you can enjoy your trip we sure did. The pools are big and beautiful they also have a hammock area which I wasn't able to get too but geesh there are plenty of them to enjoy. Peacocks are beautiful and walk up to the pool area not bothering just looking. The secluded beach is great and take those water glasses so you can see and swim with the fish. The food is great in the restaurants and sure its pricey but well worth it. Drinks are also expensive but hey your on vacation what the heck! We rented cars and vans since we were playing baseball but the taxis were expensive so we either took the cars or walked or rode the bus once. It was worth renting the car but not too many parking places. Old San Juan was fun to shop and the prices are great for souvenirs. Across the street from the hotel is a Subway if you like sandwiches all the time which the kids did. Not far is a Sizzler but you would have to drive or take a taxiOur hotel stay at the Caribe was wonderful and I thank the TripAdvisor for letting others post reviews and pictures so we know what to expect. It helped me so much and I was not dissapointed with my stay at all and neither were 